Fisting

Fisting, handballing, fist-fucking, brachiovaginal, or brachioproctic insertion{"citetype": "book", "year": "1991", "title": "Trust\u2014the Hand Book: A Guide to the Sensual and Spiritual Art of Handballing", "url": "https://books.google.com/books?id=o1ZvK2UC4FQC", "location": "San Francisco", "publisher": "Alamo Square Press", "pages": "46\u201347, 58", "isbn": "978-0-9624751-5-3", "accessdate": "March 4, 2014", "last": "Herrman", "first": "Bert"} is a sexual activity that involves inserting a hand into the vagina or rectum.[2] Once insertion is complete, the fingers are either clenched into a fist or kept straight. Fisting may be performed without a partner, but it is most often a partnered activity.

History
Fisting's emergence as a popular sexual practice is commonly attributed to gay male culture and it may not have existed until the twentieth century.{"citetype": "book", "last1": "Damousi", "first1": "Joy", "last2": "Reynolds", "first2": "Robert", "year": "2003", "title": "History on the Couch: Essays in History and Psychoanalysis", "url": "https://books.google.com/books?id=f9NIWYP7MmkC&pg=PA57", "publisher": "[[Melbourne University]]", "page": "57", "isbn": "052285057X", "accessdate": "February 24, 2016"}{"citetype": "book", "year": "2004", "title": "The Violet Hour: The Violet Quill and the Making of Gay Culture", "url": "https://books.google.com/books?id=Yam1zo4yUlsC&pg=PA206", "publisher": "[[Columbia University Press]]", "pages": "206\u2013207", "isbn": "0231503830", "accessdate": "February 24, 2016", "author": "David Bergman"}{"citetype": "book", "date": "January 2006", "title": "Queering Gay and Lesbian Studies", "url": "https://books.google.com/books?id=5AGKA8l9ADYC&pg=PA90", "publisher": "[[University of Illinois Press]]", "page": "90", "isbn": "978-0-252-03031-4", "accessdate": "October 9, 2014", "last": "Piontek", "first": "Thomas"} Robert Morgan Lawrence, a sex educator, however, believes the practice dates back thousands of years.{"citetype": "book", "date": "1998", "title": "The Ultimate Guide to Anal Sex for Women", "url": "https://books.google.com/books?id=wE4gAQAAIAAJ", "location": "Page 103", "isbn": "9781573440288", "last": "Taormino", "first": "T."}  The most famous fisting club in the world was the Catacombs, located in San Francisco, which operated during the 1970s and 1980s.{"citetype": "web", "url": "http://occupytampa.org/files/tristan/introfem/final/introfem%20final%20final/Gayle_S._Rubin_Deviations_A_Gayle_Rubin_Reader_a_John_Hope_Franklin_Center_Book__2011.pdf", "title": "Archived copy", "accessdate": "September 30, 2014", "urlstatus": "dead", "archiveurl": "https://web.archive.org/web/20141006082917/http://occupytampa.org/files/tristan/introfem/final/introfem%20final%20final/Gayle_S._Rubin_Deviations_A_Gayle_Rubin_Reader_a_John_Hope_Franklin_Center_Book__2011.pdf", "archivedate": "October 6, 2014"} The Handball Express was another such club.{"citetype": "web", "url": "http://www.ericrofes.com/pdf/70s_Walking_Tour.pdf", "title": "Archived copy", "accessdate": "November 24, 2014", "urlstatus": "dead", "archiveurl": "https://web.archive.org/web/20141031170033/http://www.ericrofes.com/pdf/70s_Walking_Tour.pdf", "archivedate": "October 31, 2014"} Crisco was commonly used as a lubricant, before more specialized personal lubricants became available.
In the 1980s, it was assumed that unprotected fisting—which often produces small injuries to the anus, permitting microorganisms access to the blood—was an easy route for transmission of HIV. This, combined with sexual squeamishness towards the public fisting culture in gay establishments of San Francisco, led gay writer Randy Shilts to successfully campaign for the closure of venues, such as gay bathhouses and sex clubs, that openly permitted it.[9] Fisting gradually returned as a sexual practice over the next 30 years.
The San Francisco South of Market Leather History Alley consists of four works of art along Ringold Alley honoring leather culture; it opened in 2017.{"citetype": "web", "url": "http://www.artandarchitecture-sf.com/ringold-alleys-leather-memoir.html", "title": "Reginold Alley's Leather Memoir", "date": "July 17, 2017", "website": "Public Art and Architecture from Around the World", "publisher": "Art and Architecture", "accessdate": "July 7, 2018", "author": "Cindy"}{"citetype": "web", "url": "https://www.jweekly.com/2018/06/21/honoring-gay-leather-culture-with-art-installation-in-soma-alleyway/", "title": "Honoring gay leather culture with art installation in SoMa alleyway \u2013 J", "last": "Paull", "first": "Laura", "date": "June 21, 2018", "publisher": "Jweekly.com", "accessdate": "June 23, 2018"} One of the works of art is metal bootprints along the curb which honor 28 people who were an important part of the leather communities of San Francisco; those honored include Steve McEachern, owner of the fisting club the Catacombs, and Bert Herman, leader of the fisting community, author, and publisher.{"citetype": "web", "url": "http://www.artandarchitecture-sf.com/ringold-alleys-leather-memoir.html", "title": "Reginold Alley's Leather Memoir", "date": "July 17, 2017", "website": "Public Art and Architecture from Around the World", "publisher": "Art and Architecture", "accessdate": "July 7, 2018", "author": "Cindy"}{"citetype": "web", "url": "https://www.jweekly.com/2018/06/21/honoring-gay-leather-culture-with-art-installation-in-soma-alleyway/", "title": "Honoring gay leather culture with art installation in SoMa alleyway \u2013 J", "last": "Paull", "first": "Laura", "date": "June 21, 2018", "publisher": "Jweekly.com", "accessdate": "June 23, 2018"}

Techniques
The "Silent Duck", also called "Duck-Billing", is the technique often used in which the person engaging in hand insertion shapes the hand to resemble a duck's beak. Typically, fisting does not involve forcing the clenched fist into the vagina or rectum; this is a practice called "punching". Instead, all five fingers are kept straight and held as close together as possible (forming the beak-like "duck"), then slowly inserted into a well lubricated vagina or rectum.{"citetype": "book", "year": "1991", "title": "Trust\u2014the Hand Book: A Guide to the Sensual and Spiritual Art of Handballing", "url": "https://books.google.com/books?id=o1ZvK2UC4FQC", "location": "San Francisco", "publisher": "Alamo Square Press", "pages": "46\u201347, 58", "isbn": "978-0-9624751-5-3", "accessdate": "March 4, 2014", "last": "Herrman", "first": "Bert"}
In more vigorous forms of fisting, such as "punching" or "punchfisting", a fully clenched fist may be inserted and withdrawn slowly.
Fistees who are more experienced may take two fists (double-fisting). In the case of double-fisting, pleasure is derived more from the stretching of the anus or vagina than from the thrusting (in-and-out) movement of hands.{"citetype": "book", "year": "1991", "title": "Trust\u2014the Hand Book: A Guide to the Sensual and Spiritual Art of Handballing", "url": "https://books.google.com/books?id=o1ZvK2UC4FQC", "location": "San Francisco", "publisher": "Alamo Square Press", "pages": "46\u201347, 58", "isbn": "978-0-9624751-5-3", "accessdate": "March 4, 2014", "last": "Herrman", "first": "Bert"}

Risks
Fisting can cause laceration or perforation of the vagina, perineum, rectum, or colon, resulting in serious injury{"citetype": "journal", "last2": "Giles", "first2": "A.", "last3": "Nelson", "first3": "M.", "date": "2004", "title": "Sexual trauma associated with fisting and recreational drugs", "journal": "[[Sexually Transmitted Infections (journal)|Sexually Transmitted Infections]]", "volume": "80", "issue": "6", "pages": "469\u2013470", "doi": "10.1136/sti.2004.011171", "pmc": "1744939", "pmid": "15572616", "last": "Cohen", "first": "C. E."} and even death.{"citetype": "journal", "last2": "Strehler", "first2": "Marco", "last3": "Dettmeyer", "first3": "Reinhard", "last4": "Madea", "first4": "B.", "date": "2007", "title": "Death after anal &quot;fisting&quot;", "journal": "Archiv f\u00fcr Kriminologie", "volume": "221", "issue": "1\u20132", "pages": "28\u201335", "pmid": "18389861", "last": "Preuss", "first": "Johanna"}{"citetype": "journal", "date": "1987", "title": "Delayed death from &quot;fisting&quot;", "journal": "The American Journal of Forensic Medicine and Pathology", "volume": "8", "issue": "1", "page": "91", "doi": "10.1097/00000433-198703000-00026", "last": "Torre", "first": "Carlo"}{"citetype": "journal", "last2": "McCormick", "first2": "George M.", "date": "1989", "title": "Vaginal &quot;fisting&quot; as a cause of death", "journal": "The American Journal of Forensic Medicine and Pathology", "volume": "10", "issue": "1", "pages": "73\u201375", "doi": "10.1097/00000433-198903000-00019", "last": "Fain", "first": "Dawn B."}{"citetype": "journal", "date": "1983", "title": "Sexual abuse and death of an elderly lady by &quot;fisting&quot;", "journal": "The American Journal of Forensic Medicine and Pathology", "volume": "4", "issue": "4", "pages": "347\u2013350", "doi": "10.1097/00000433-198312000-00013", "last": "Reay", "first": "Donald T.", "author2": "John W. Eisele"} In addition, sexual activities that cause air to enter the vagina can lead to a fatal air embolism, and the risk is probably even higher during pregnancy.{"citetype": "journal", "date": "1994", "title": "Air embolism death of a pregnant woman secondary to orogenital sex", "journal": "Academic Emergency Medicine", "volume": "1", "issue": "6", "pages": "555\u2013558", "doi": "10.1111/j.1553-2712.1994.tb02552.x", "last": "Kaiser", "first": "Rachel T."}
Anal fisting carries risks of colorectal perforation; participants are advised to use latex gloves and lubricant,{"citetype": "book", "year": "2008", "title": "HIVAIDS Care & Counselling", "url": "https://books.google.com/books?id=BZQ9LqUHDWYC&pg=PA156", "edition": "4", "publisher": "Pearson South Africa", "page": "156", "isbn": "978-1-77025-171-7", "accessdate": "March 4, 2014", "last": "Dyk", "first": "Alta C. Van"} and designate a safeword, the utterance of which will call an immediate halt to the activity. The practice, along with the insertion of hard objects into the anus, has been significantly related to the traumatization of the rectal mucosa in increasing the likelihood of infection, including Hepatitis B.{"citetype": "book", "date": "January 15, 1994", "title": "AIDS and Behavior: An Integrated Approach", "url": "https://books.google.com/books?id=wq7fSNgUZKQC", "publisher": "National Academies Press", "page": "49", "isbn": "978-0-309-05093-7", "accessdate": "March 4, 2014", "last": "Auerbach", "first": "Judith"}

Legal status
In the United Kingdom fisting is legal to perform;{"citetype": "news", "date": "August 8, 2012", "title": "Extreme porn trial: consensual sex and the state &#124; Myles Jackman &#124; Law &#124; guardian.co.uk", "url": "https://www.theguardian.com/law/2012/aug/08/extreme-porn-trial-simon-walsh", "location": "London", "accessdate": "January 4, 2013", "author": "Myles Jackman", "newspaper": "Guardian"} however, the Crown Prosecution Service considers publication of fisting material to be grounds for prosecution under the Obscene Publications Act 1959.{"citetype": "web", "url": "http://www.cps.gov.uk/legal/l_to_o/obscene_publications/#a05", "title": "Obscene publications: Legal Guidance: The Crown Prosecution Service", "publisher": "Crown Prosecution Service", "accessdate": "August 27, 2014"} Despite the CPS's guidance, in the case of R v Peacock in 2012, Michael Peacock was found not guilty of breaching the Obscene Publications Act for selling DVDs containing anal fisting.{"citetype": "news", "date": "January 7, 2012", "title": "Obscenity law in doubt after jury acquits distributor of gay pornography", "url": "https://www.theguardian.com/law/2012/jan/07/obscene-publications-act-future-doubt", "accessdate": "January 7, 2012", "newspaper": "The Guardian", "author1": "Beaumont, Peter", "author2": "Hodgson, Nichi"} There was also an unsuccessful extreme pornography prosecution in 2012 where it was argued by the prosecution that images of anal fisting constitute extreme pornography and thus are illegal to possess because the act is "likely to result in serious injury to a person's anus, breasts or genitals".{"citetype": "news", "date": "August 8, 2012", "title": "Extreme porn trial: consensual sex and the state &#124; Myles Jackman &#124; Law &#124; guardian.co.uk", "url": "https://www.theguardian.com/law/2012/aug/08/extreme-porn-trial-simon-walsh", "location": "London", "accessdate": "January 4, 2013", "author": "Myles Jackman", "newspaper": "Guardian"}
