In the United States, according to attorney Allan Gelbard there is nothing "per se illegal" about any pornography so long as it is not child pornography, however, it can be found to be obscene. Fisting is on the Cambria List, a list of sex acts which may be prosecutable under U.S. obscenity law, created by lawyer Paul Cambria in 2001. The list is intended to act as guidelines to help producers avoid obscenity lawsuits.{"citetype": "news", "date": "October 21, 2014", "title": "Is fisting the Internet's last taboo sex act?", "url": "https://www.dailydot.com/irl/fisting-taboo-law/", "work": "The Daily Dot", "language": "en-US", "accessdate": "March 3, 2018"}
